Privacy Policy
At Goblin.Tools, we care about your privacy and understand that it is important to you.
That's why we've created this simple privacy policy to explain how we handle your information. Please take a moment to read through it.
Information we collect
We only collect the bare minimum of information necessary for the site to function properly and to allow us to maintain it. When you use Goblin.Tools, we store some data locally in your browser (such as settings and preferences). 
    We also use Microsoft Clarity and Simple Analytics to analyse user behaviour. This data has no personally identifiable information or any text you input, and does not track you or use cookies.
How we use your information
We use the information stored in your browser to personalize your experience on Goblin.Tools. This data stays on your device and is not sent to us or any third party.
Sharing your information with OpenAI
When you use our services that rely on OpenAI's technology, we send the necessary input data to OpenAI's servers to process your request. We do not store this data on our servers, and we do not share it with any other third party.
    OpenAI's privacy policy can be found on at
https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy
. Goblin.tools and OpenAI do not get any information about who submitted what requests, or where from.
Data security
We are committed to ensuring the security of your information. All data stored in your browser is kept secure and is not accessible by anyone else. We do not have access to this data ourselves.
Changes to this policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, so please check back periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.
Contact us
If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or the way we handle your information, please feel free to contact us at support@goblin.tools.
By using Goblin.Tools, you agree to the terms of this privacy policy.
